# Next.js Rules

- Use the App Router structure, using `page.tsx` files in the routing directory.
- Client components must be explicitly marked with `'use client'` at the top of the file.
- Directory names use kebab-case (e.g. `components/auth-form`), component files use PascalCase.
- Prefer named exports over default exports, i.e., use `export function Button() { /* ... */ }` instead of `export default function Button() { /* ... */ }`.
- Try to minimize `'use client'` directives:
  - Keep most components as React Server Components (RSC)
  - Use client components only when needed, wrapped with `Suspense` with fallback UI
  - Create small client component wrappers for interactive elements
- Try to avoid unnecessary `useState` and `useEffect`:
  - Use server components for data fetching
  - Use React Server Actions to handle forms
  - Use URL search parameters for shared state
- Use `nuqs` to manage URL search parameter state